  dnaBarcode: { itsClade: "Agaricus section Arvenses (clade containing A. arvensis, A. silvicola, A. augustus and allies; characterized by yellow KOH reaction and almond/anise odor)", keyPaper: "Kerrigan, R.W. (2016) Agaricus of North America - Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden Vol. 114; Zhao et al. (2011) Towards standardizing taxonomic ranks using divergence times - a case study for reconstruction of the Agaricus taxonomic system. Fungal Diversity 51:279-309", notes: "Section Arvenses is well-supported by ITS1, ITS2, and 5.8S sequence data. Some smaller, less-scaled PNW collections may represent cryptic sister taxa; critical molecular studies are not yet complete (per Burke Herbarium / Trudell & Ammirati 2009)." },
