  microhabitat: { slopeAspect: null, soilPh: [6.0, 7.5], soilTexture: "loam to clay-loam pasture soils enriched with decomposing grass thatch and (often) herbivore dung; tolerates compacted turf", moisturePreference: "moist but well-drained; fruits 2-6 days after sustained rain on soils that do not waterlog", indicatorPlants: ["Lolium perenne (perennial ryegrass)", "Festuca rubra (red fescue)", "Trifolium repens (white clover)", "Agrostis spp. (bentgrasses)", "Poa pratensis (Kentucky bluegrass)", "Plantago lanceolata (ribwort plantain)"], notes: "Strongly associated with grazed or mown grasslands, especially old horse and sheep pastures; declines markedly on synthetically fertilized or herbicide-treated turf. Often forms fairy rings in long-undisturbed sod." },
