  substrate: "Soil and forest duff under ectomycorrhizal conifer and birch hosts; not lignicolous; frequently fruits in mossy openings, trail edges, and disturbed mineral soil.",
  habitat: "Coniferous and mixed conifer-hardwood forests across the PNW; common from coastal Sitka spruce-hemlock forests to interior pine and Douglas-fir stands; also in urban parks and ornamental plantings, particularly under introduced birch and pine; the western North American form is dominantly Amanita muscaria var. flavivolvata (yellow-warted), with var. guessowii (yellow-orange cap) also present in some areas.",
  elevationM: { min: 0, max: 2500 },
