    cap: "5-15 cm (occasionally to 20 cm); hemispheric then convex to broadly convex and finally plane; viscid when fresh, soon dry; warm pale tan, honey-yellow, ochre-brown to dark hazel or umber-brown, often darker in the disc and paler at the margin; surface decorated with numerous small, soft, cottony, distinctly WHITE (never yellow) universal-veil warts that are easily washed off by rain; margin distinctly striate-sulcate at maturity (a key feature separating it from the non-striate A. muscaria).",
