    consensus: "strong",
    disputeNotes: "All consulted sources (MykoWeb TFWNA, MushroomExpert/Kuo, PNW Key Council/SVIMS, Vancouver Mycological Society, Wikipedia A. pantherinoides, iNaturalist, Tulloss/Amanitaceae.org, Satora et al. 2006, Vendramin & Brvar 2014, MDPI 2025 review, Trudell & Ammirati 2009) agree on the species' toxicity, isoxazole-toxin chemistry, mycorrhizal ecology, morphological characters, and PNW range. The only active taxonomic dispute is nomenclatural: whether PNW material should be called A. pantherinoides (Murrill 1912, accepted by Tulloss and Vancouver Mycological Society), A. pantherina var. pantherinoides (Jenkins 1979), an undescribed Tulloss species, or simply A. pantherina sensu lato. This does NOT affect field safety guidance - all are toxic and treated identically."
