    cap: "5-15 cm, convex becoming flat, smooth and viscid (sticky) when moist, shiny when dry; color highly variable: olive-green, yellowish-green, bronze, brownish, or pale to nearly white; faint radial fibrils; margin not striate; California specimens often display mustard-yellow tones.",
