    keyPaper: "Bas, C. (1969). Morphology and subdivision of Amanita and a monograph of its section Lepidella. Persoonia 5(3): 285-579 (A. smithiana p. 418-419). Tulloss, R.E. & Lindgren, J.E. (1992). Amanita smithiana - taxonomy, distribution, and poisonings. Mycotaxon 45: 373-387.",
    notes: "Type description by Cornelis Bas in 1969 from Pacific Northwest material collected by Alexander H. Smith. Kirchmair et al. (2012, Nephrol Dial Transplant 27:1380-1386) tested 20 Amanita species for the smithiana-type toxin and confirmed shared chemistry across several white section-Lepidella amanitas on both sides of the Atlantic, implying conservation of the toxin biosynthesis pathway within the section."
