  microhabitat: { slopeAspect: null, soilPh: [4.5, 6.0], soilTexture: "well-drained sandy loams to humus-rich duff over glacial till or coastal sands", moisturePreference: "consistently moist but well-drained; thrives in oceanic hyperhumid conifer forests and montane snowmelt-fed slopes", indicatorPlants: ["Vaccinium ovatum", "Vaccinium parvifolium", "Gaultheria shallon", "Hylocomium splendens", "Rhytidiadelphus loreus", "Linnaea borealis", "Cornus canadensis"], notes: "Strongly associated with thick moss carpets (Hylocomium, Rhytidiadelphus) under mature Sitka spruce on the coast and feather-moss carpets under Engelmann spruce inland; absent from pure Douglas-fir or pure hemlock stands lacking spruce or pine component" },
