  dnaBarcode: { itsClade: "Cantharellus cibarius species complex, subgenus Cantharellus, sister to C. cibarius sensu stricto and C. enelensis within a Holarctic spruce-associated subclade", keyPaper: "Redhead, S.A., Norvell, L.L. & Danell, E. (1997). Cantharellus formosus and the Pacific Golden Chanterelle harvest in western North America. Mycotaxon 65: 285-322 (protologue as C. cibarius var. roseocanus); raised to species in Redhead (2012) Index Fungorum 5:1; ITS placement supported by Moncalvo et al. (2006) Mycologia 98(6): 937-948 and Foltz, Perez & Volk (2013) Mycologia 105(2): 447-461", notes: "Pacific Coast and Rocky Mountain collections show some macromorphological divergence; additional ITS/TEF1 sequencing recommended to test whether interior populations represent a distinct phylogenetic species (per Siegel 2021 IUCN assessment)" },
