  dnaBarcode: { itsClade: "Clade 9 in Das et al. (2015) LSU phylogeny of Cantharellus; sister to the C. cibarius / C. formosus / C. cascadensis groups within western North American Cantharellus", keyPaper: "Das, K., Hembrom, M.E., Parihar, A. & Buyck, B. (2015). New records of Cantharellus species from the northwestern Himalayas of India. IMA Fungus / Mycoscience phylogenetic study (LSU + ITS).", notes: "Type material at MICH (syntype 10074); NCBI Taxonomy ID 75104. Limited ITS sequence coverage in public databases for this species; LSU resolves it as a distinct monophyletic lineage among western North American white-spored chanterelles." },
  verification: { sourcesAgreeing: 6, lastVerified: "2026-05-23", consensus: "strong", disputeNotes: "Minor disagreement on reported spore size range (MykoWeb 7.5-9 x 5-6 um vs. MushroomExpert 6-8.5 x 4-5 um); the union 6-9 x 4-6 um spans both. Habitat reports differ on second-growth tolerance: Dunham et al. (2006) emphasize old-growth affinity, while some popular guides describe it as found 'frequently under second-growth conifers.'" }
