  dnaBarcode: { itsClade: "/subalpinum clade within Catathelasma (sister to Asian C. laorentou and C. subalpinum); North American sequences labeled 'C. ventricosum' in GenBank cluster here, though a verified type sequence is still lacking", keyPaper: "Ge Z-W, Wu J-Y, Hao Y-J, Zhang Q, An Y-F, Ryberg M (2020). The genus Catathelasma (Catathelasmataceae, Basidiomycota) in China. MycoKeys 62: 123-138. doi:10.3897/mycokeys.62.36633", notes: "Multi-locus phylogeny (ITS + LSU/28S + TEF1) resolves Catathelasma into two monophyletic clades (/subalpinum and /imperiale). PNW C. ventricosum sequences match east-coast North American collections in published trees; a type-locality (NY) epitype sequence is still desirable. See also Vizzini et al. (2020) Fungal Diversity 101: 211-259 for family-level (Biannulariaceae) placement." },
  verification: { sourcesAgreeing: 5, lastVerified: "2026-05-23", consensus: "strong", disputeNotes: "Minor unresolved taxonomic question: whether PNW collections are conspecific with the eastern North American type of C. ventricosum (Peck) Singer; Ge et al. 2020 leave open the possibility that some southeastern US sequences may represent a distinct species pending an epitype sequence. Spore size ranges vary slightly between sources (e.g., 7-9 x 4.5-6 from a Maryland collection vs. 9-13 x 4-6 from Kuo/standard floras); the broader 9-13 x 4-6 range is used here." }
