  substrate: "Lignicolous - decaying stumps, logs, fallen branches, and buried roots of both coniferous and deciduous trees; occasionally appearing terrestrial when fruiting from buried wood.",
  habitat: "Mixed and conifer-dominated forests throughout the PNW; especially abundant on second-growth Douglas-fir stumps, decaying alder, and rotting hardwood debris; common in disturbed areas, urban parks, and along trails wherever dead wood is present.",
