    stem: "5-12 cm long, 0.4-1.0 cm thick; equal or slightly tapered; sulphur-yellow above, becoming rusty-brown to orange-brown toward the base; longitudinally fibrillose; cortinate veil (cobwebby partial veil) leaves only an ephemeral fibrillose ring zone, often darkened by trapped spores; stems typically fused at the base in dense fascicles.",
    fleshColor: "Yellow throughout; unchanging when cut; thin in cap, more fibrous in stem.",
    sporePrintColor: "Purple-brown to dark purple-black",
    odor: "Mild, mushroomy, not distinctive.",
    sizeCm: "Cap 2-7 cm; stem 5-12 x 0.4-1.0 cm"
