      keyFeatures: ["two-toned hygrophanous cap","membranous ring","scaly stem below ring","cinnamon-brown spore print"],
      distinguishingFeature: "Caps two-toned (hygrophanous - brown when wet, paler when dry), with a persistent membranous ring on the stem and a scaly stem below the ring; spore print cinnamon-brown (not purple-brown); choice edible in Europe but dangerously similar to Galerina marginata."
