  microhabitat: { slopeAspect: null, soilPh: [5.5, 7.5], soilTexture: "Loamy to sandy-loam turf soils with well-developed thatch layer; tolerates compacted urban/suburban soils and regularly mown sod", moisturePreference: "Mesic to seasonally moist; fruits flush after warm rain or irrigation but the mycelium tolerates summer drought thanks to high tissue trehalose content", indicatorPlants: ["Lolium perenne (perennial ryegrass)", "Festuca rubra (red fescue)", "Poa pratensis (Kentucky bluegrass)", "Agrostis spp. (bentgrasses)", "Trifolium repens (white clover)", "Taraxacum officinale (common dandelion)"], notes: "Forms classic 'Type II' fairy rings with a zone of stimulated (darker green) and/or necrotic (browned) grass; HCN release and hydrophobic mycelial mat in the necrotic zone alter local soil water relations and inhibit grass roots within ~25 cm of the ring front." },
