  dnaBarcode: { itsClade: "Thelephoraceae, order Thelephorales; Polyozellus forms a well-supported monophyletic clade sister to Thelephora/Tomentella, splitting into a small-spored subclade (P. multiplex s.s. + P. atrolazulinus) and a large-spored subclade (P. mariae, P. marymargaretae, P. purpureoniger). UNITE species hypothesis SH188416.07FU represents the P. mariae lineage; P. multiplex s.s. anchored by GenBank ITS accessions deposited with the Voitk et al. 2017 study.", keyPaper: "Voitk A, Saar I, Trudell S, Spirin V, Beug M, Koljalg U. 2017. Polyozellus multiplex (Thelephorales) is a species complex containing four new species. Mycologia 109(6):975-992. doi:10.1080/00275514.2017.1416246", notes: "ITS sequencing is required to distinguish PNW collections, which may represent P. multiplex s.s., P. atrolazulinus, P. marymargaretae, or P. purpureoniger rather than a single biological species. Morphological clues (spore size, pileipellis color retention, margin shape) only partly resolve identity." },
  verification: { sourcesAgreeing: 7, lastVerified: "2026-05-23", consensus: "strong", disputeNotes: "Strong consensus on morphology, ecology, edibility, and bioactivity. Taxonomy is in flux: many historic PNW 'Polyozellus multiplex' records are now reassigned to P. atrolazulinus or P. marymargaretae (Voitk et al. 2017), so the species-level identity of any uncollected sighting is provisional without ITS data." }
