  habitat: "Open to moderately dense pine and mixed conifer forests, particularly on well-drained sandy to gravelly soils; in the PNW most commonly in ponderosa-pine and mixed ponderosa-Douglas-fir stands east of the Cascade crest, occasionally west-side in dry conifer forest; in eastern North America widespread under pitch, loblolly, longleaf, and shortleaf pines.",
